                    "company": "iGEM Competition",
                    "description": "Grand Prize (Overgrad), Best Track (Diagnostics), Best Wiki, Best Inclusion, and Best Supporting Entrepreneurship. Nominated for Best Poster, Best Human Practices, Best Model, and Best Basic Part. \n\nI was responsible for the laboratory and overall safety and security of the project. In addition, I performed several experiments, worked on the diagnostic kit design and helped shoot our project and promotion videos. \n\n'The COVID-19 pandemic demonstrated the importance of testing, as isolating infected individuals is crucial to restrict the spread of a disease. However, delayed measures and our inability to meet the increasing demand for diagnostic tests at the start of the pandemic caused us to lose control. Inspired by the current COVID-19 pandemic and the lack of accessible testing, we set out to develop a novel, point-of-care rapid diagnostic kit: RAPIDEMIC. Throughout several months, we studied the field of molecular diagnostics and performed experiments, which eventually led to the preliminary proof for our detection method.'",
